body:
Given this `.vlt` file, one might expect there will be no FOO warnings from `file.sv` at all.

```
`verilator_config
lint_off -rule FOO -file "file.sv"
```

However, if file.sv looks like this:

```systemverilog
   int a;
   /* verilator lint_off FOO */
   int b;
   /* verilator lint_on FOO */
   int c;
```

The `lint_on` in the code turns the warning back on for the rest of the lines following it, effectively ignoring the directive from the control file.

Don't think this is intentional. Can we make the effect of the control files sticky? I suspect that needs a second bitset in the message enable sets that are only affected by the control file directives, which should be ok.

code_blocks:
`verilator_config
lint_off -rule FOO -file "file.sv"
   int a;
   /* verilator lint_off FOO */
   int b;
   /* verilator lint_on FOO */
   int c;
